# Vanilla JS DOM - jQuery Replacement

Always use native DOM APIs instead of jQuery:

## Element Selection
```javascript
// Instead of: $('.selector')
document.querySelectorAll('.selector')

// Instead of: $('#id')  
document.querySelector('#id')

// Instead of: $('.selector').length > 0
document.querySelector('.selector') !== null
```

## Content Manipulation
```javascript
// Instead of: $('#id').text('content')
document.querySelector('#id').textContent = 'content'

// Instead of: $('#id').html('<span>content</span>')
document.querySelector('#id').innerHTML = '<span>content</span>'

// Instead of: $('#id').val('value')
document.querySelector('#id').value = 'value'
```

## Event Handling
```javascript
// Instead of: $('.btn').on('click', handler)
document.querySelector('.btn').addEventListener('click', handler)

// Event delegation:
document.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
  if (e.target.matches('.btn')) {
    handler(e);
  }
});
```

## CSS Classes
```javascript
// Instead of: $('.el').addClass('class')
document.querySelector('.el').classList.add('class')

// Instead of: $('.el').removeClass('class')
document.querySelector('.el').classList.remove('class')

// Instead of: $('.el').toggleClass('class')
document.querySelector('.el').classList.toggle('class')
```

## Styles
```javascript
// Instead of: $('.el').css('color', 'red')
document.querySelector('.el').style.color = 'red'

// Multiple styles:
const el = document.querySelector('.el');
Object.assign(el.style, { color: 'red', fontSize: '16px' });
```

## DOM Ready
```javascript
// Instead of: $(document).ready(callback)
if (document.readyState === 'loading') {
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', callback);
} else {
  callback();
}
```